    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nQuickFix and LocationList windows do not respect the `statusline` option when `laststatus=3` (global statusline).\r\nThey show the default statusline information, different from the custom value set by users / plugins.\r\n\r\n#### Left: Normal window & Right: QuickFix window\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/45595032/a226dbb5-6333-4c1e-8c0f-74a3fc0eeeb8)![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/45595032/f31a3103-3164-4306-a9a4-33993a7450a9)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open neovim using `$ nvim -u NORC`.\r\n2. Execute `:set laststatus=3 statusline=<testing>`. Notice that the statusline now shows the string \"\\<testing>\".\r\n    Also, `:set winbar=%f` for the same appearance as in the screenshot. Unrelated to bug, just for visualization.\r\n4. Execute `:copen`. Notice that the statusline now shows the default format string, and not the string set in Step 2.\r\n    This behavior can be seen for `:lopen` as well.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nCustom `statusline` option should apply to the windows with `qf` filetype buffers.\r\n\r\nThis is caused due to the code (line 13-18 at the time of posting) in ftplugin file for [quickfix](runtime/ftplugin/qf.vim) filetype. This does not check for the global statusline, i.e `laststatus==3` when locally modifying the `statusline` option.\r\n\r\nIf this is undesirable behavior and a bug, I am more than happy to submit a PR to fix this after the necessary discussion.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2258+g1405e5c8c\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno, vim does not have laststatus=3 option\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nWindows 10 AND Ubuntu 20.04\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nnvim-win64.msi nightly release on Windows AND nightly PPA using apt on Linux",
